About Am I Pwned?

PerfektBlue

Universal 1-click RCE exploit to PWN automotive industry

The sophisticated attack chain leveraging multiple vulnerabilities in a specific Bluetooth implementation that leads to Remote Code Execution on millions of vehicles. The original author of these findings is @konatabrk

Slides Video PCA Website

Research

The vulnerability research project was conducted while working at PCA. During the work I was able to confirm that Volkswagen, Skoda, BMW, Mercedes-Benz and Audi head units are affected by PerfektBlue. These findings were responsibly discloused to OpenSynergy - the original vendor of BlueSDK.

Freetime

In my freetime I decided to investigate if some other devices might be affected by PerfektBlue. Below is an incomplete list of potentially vulnerable devices I was able to find. I don't claim that all device in the table are 100% affected to PerfektBlue, there might be some incorrections.

Device Report

Usually, when a vendor integrates a Bluetooth stack into their products, they must pass a Bluetooth certification (at least, from my understanding). Hence, to find all the possibly affected devices, the one can use this certification and match the Bluetooth product name. Conveniently, device.report website provides such kind of information, so it was the main source for locating all the devices in the table.

The table incorporates all the necessary information about each possibly affected device, including their certification date. Remember that devices with old certification date might be unaffected to PerfektBlue, mostly because they could switch to another Bluetooth stack.
